5.6 Riddle Refinement Engine (Spec A)

Objective: A semi-automated pipeline to author, vet, version, deploy, and retrospectively score verses (riddles) ensuring uniqueness, fairness, thematic resonance, difficulty calibration, and low brute‚Äëforce surface.

a. Data Model

// riddles/season0/S0-11.json (example)
{
"id": "S0-11",
"tier": 2,
"public": "I divide every circle yet I‚Äôm never a line.",
"themes": ["geometry", "abstraction"],
"expectedSolveMinutes": 35,
"answerInternal": "radius",          // off-chain only
"fallbackHints": [
"I connect center and edge.",
"Half a span the whole depends on."
],
"meta": {
"syllablePattern": "4-4-5-4 (optional)",
"ambiguityScore": 0.08,              // ML / heuristic (0‚Äì1)
"testGroup": ["r1","r2","r3"],
"meanSolveTimeMin": 33,
"stdDev": 6,
"solveAttempts": 5,
"uniqueAnswers": ["radius"],
"version": 2
}
}

b. Pipeline Stages

Stage	Tooling	Pass / Fail Criteria	Output

Draft	Human ideation template	Conforms to tone, ‚â§ 2 candidate answers	Raw JSON v0
Structure Scan	Linter (regex syllable & banned words)	No banned leakage (answer literal)	Annotated JSON
Ambiguity Heuristic	Keyword divergence & embedding similarity vs known answers	AmbiguityScore < 0.25	Score updated
Blind Test	Script dispatch to tester pool (Discord bot DM)	‚â•60% testers solve within target window; no alt consensus	Stats merged
Governance Gate (future)	Snapshot off-chain vote (tiers ‚â•3)	Quorum + majority	Marked approved
Hash Commit	CLI: hash-verse (solution + nonce)	Reproducible keccak	Hash stored on-chain via setVerse

c. CLI Utilities (Node / TS)

npx wl verse:new ‚Üí scaffolds JSON

npx wl verse:test S0-11 ‚Üí pushes to testers, collects solve times

npx wl verse:hash S0-11 --nonce 23 ‚Üí prints keccak256(abi.encodePacked(answer, nonce))

npx wl verse:report season0 ‚Üí aggregates difficulty drift (actual vs expected)

d. Metrics & Alerts

Metric	Source	Threshold	Action

Mean Solve Time Deviation	Subgraph (VerseSet/Solved)	> +100% expected	Add hint / adjust future tier weights
Early Solve Concentration	% of solves by top 1 address per 5 verses	>40%	Introduce cooldown / reputation dampening
Ambiguity Incidents	Post-solve disputes logged	>2 per season	Tighten linter & review rubric

e. Future ML Assist (Optional)

Embedding Similarity of candidate verses vs existing to detect near-duplicates.

Answer Plausibility Generator: LLM enumerates alternative answers; if >1 strongly plausible ‚Üí revise.


