5.10 Ethical & Capability Safeguards ‚Äì ‚ÄúSeizing the Keys‚Äù Layer

Your phrase ‚Äúsupercede superhuman abilities as incubant unlocking if you seize the keys‚Äù is reframed as a Guardian Ethos: advanced protocol capabilities (‚ÄúKeys‚Äù) must never centralize latent ‚Äòsuperhuman‚Äô leverage (e.g., undisclosed algorithmic advantage, AI-generated riddles with opaque difficulty).

Key Domain	Potential ‚ÄòSuperhuman‚Äô Drift	Safeguard

AI Riddle Generation	Unfair complexity spike	Mandate human editorial + publish complexity rubric
Insider Advance Notice	Early solving for team wallets	Enforced nda + commit timestamps + optional public pre-commit queue
Adaptive Difficulty Algorithms	Invisible weighting that favors certain wallets	Open-source difficulty module + reproducible inputs
Data Advantage (Subgraph latency)	Faster event awareness for insiders	Provide public websocket & mirror endpoint docs
Moderation Power	Censoring verses or solvers silently	On-chain InvalidateVerse event with reason hash

Incubant Unlocking Protocol (Draft):

1. Proposal (community signals enabling new feature ‚Üí e.g., commit mode default).


2. Key Ceremony (multi-sig rotates to include ‚â•2 non-founding solver addresses).


3. Public Dry Run (feature shadow-enabled with telemetry only).


4. Activation Block Height pre-announced (‚â•10k blocks notice).


5. Post-Activation Audit Snapshot (hashes of new config vars).



Ethical Statement Snippet (for site):

> ‚ÄúWe do not chase superhuman scale. We refine human insight. Every key we add is witnessed, documented, and challengeable.‚Äù




