5.16 Riddle CLI Implementation (VerseOps Toolkit)

Goal: Provide a deterministic, auditable workflow for authoring, linting, testing, hashing, and reporting riddles ("verses"). Implemented as a Node.js CLI (TypeScript) published privately (@whisperledger/verseops).

a. Directory Structure

verseops/
‚îú‚îÄ package.json
‚îú‚îÄ tsconfig.json
‚îú‚îÄ src/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ index.ts              # entrypoint / command router
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ commands/
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ new.ts            # scaffold new verse JSON
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ lint.ts           # structural / leakage checks
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ test.ts           # blind test dispatch (Discord DM API hook)
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ hash.ts           # compute abi.encodePacked(solution, nonce)
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ report.ts         # aggregate season stats
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ mlCheck.ts        # ambiguity / similarity scoring
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ lib/
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ fs.ts             # file IO abstraction
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ syllables.ts      # naive syllable estimator
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ embeddings.ts     # optional ML similarity (pluggable)
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ config.ts         # global constants
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ crypto.ts         # hashing helpers
‚îú‚îÄ riddles/season0/*.json    # data (git-crypt or encrypted)
‚îî‚îÄ .env                      # DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN, OPENAI_KEY (if used)

b. Example package.json

{
"name": "@whisperledger/verseops",
